fields.name: ContentType
fields.description:
The content type of the key-value's value.
Providing a proper content-type can enable transformations of values when they are retrieved by applications.

fields.name: ETag
fields.description: An ETag indicating the state of a key-value within a configuration store.

fields.name: Key
fields.description:
The primary identifier of a key-value.
The key is used in unison with the label to uniquely identify a key-value.

fields.name: Label
fields.description:
A value used to group key-values.
The label is used in unison with the key to uniquely identify a key-value.

fields.name: LastModified
fields.description: The last time a modifying operation was performed on the given key-value.

fields.name: Locked
fields.description:
A value indicating whether the key-value is locked.
A locked key-value may not be modified until it is unlocked.

fields.name: Tags
fields.description: A dictionary of tags that can help identify what a key-value may be applicable for.
